# Resources (moko-resources)

All strings, colors, and images are placed in `moko-resources`. Hardcoded strings in Composables are forbidden.

## Structure

```
shared/common-resources/
├── build.gradle.kts
└── src/commonMain/moko-resources/
    └── base/
        └── strings.xml
```

## Setup (`common-resources/build.gradle.kts`)

```kotlin
plugins {
    alias(libs.plugins.conventionPlugin.kmpLibrary)
    alias(libs.plugins.moko.resources)
}

multiplatformResources {
    resourcesPackage.set("dev.nonoxy.kmmtemplate.res")
    resourcesClassName.set("MR")
    resourcesVisibility.set(MRVisibility.Public)
}

commonMainDependencies {
    apis(libs.moko.resources.core)
}
```

## strings.xml

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<resources>
    <!-- Common -->
    <string name="button_retry">Retry</string>
    <string name="error_loading">Loading error</string>

    <!-- {feature} -->
    <string name="{feature}_title">Title</string>
    <string name="{feature}_error_loading">Failed to load data</string>
</resources>
```

## Usage

```kotlin
import dev.icerock.moko.resources.compose.stringResource
import dev.nonoxy.kmmtemplate.res.MR

Text(text = stringResource(MR.strings.{feature}_{element}_{description}))
```

## Key Naming Rules

- `{feature}_{element}_{description}` — for feature-specific strings
- `{element}_{description}` — for shared strings
- Examples: `demo_first_title`, `button_retry`, `error_loading`

## Dependencies

`common-ui` connects `common-resources` as `api` — all UI modules automatically get access to `MR`.
